		"body": "## Summary\r\nFixes #14271\r\n\r\nCurrently, when a plugin manifest is missing the mandatory `app_min_version` field, Joplin returns a generic error: *\"This plugin doesn't support Joplin Desktop\"* (or Mobile). This is misleading as it implies a platform incompatibility rather than a missing manifest field.\r\n\r\nThis PR adds an explicit check for the `app_min_version` field to provide clear, actionable feedback to developers.\r\n\r\n## Proposed Changes\r\n- **Explicit Check:** Modified `describeIncompatibility` in `PluginService.ts` to detect a missing `app_min_version` before proceeding to platform version resolution.\r\n- **Improved Error Message:** Returns a specific localized string: _\"The plugin manifest is missing the required \"app_min_version\" field.\"_\r\n- **Regression Test:** Added a test case to `packages/lib/services/plugins/utils/isCompatible/index.test.ts` to ensure that a manifest without this field specifically triggers the new error message.\r\n\r\n## Test Plan\r\n- [x] **Manual Verification:** Confirmed the code builds correctly via `yarn watch`.\r\n- [x] **Automated Tests:** Ran the compatibility test suite in `packages/lib`.\r\n- [x] **Result:** All 24 tests passed (including the new regression test).\r\n\r\n`PASS  services/plugins/utils/isCompatible/index.test.js`",
